OL,7,FThis increased available core funding
OL,8,Fby 7.5% compared to 2023/24, but the
OL,9,Fcommittee concluded this would not
OL,10,Fcome close to addressing financial
OL,11,Fpressures across the sector, with the
OL,12,FLocal Government Association
OL,13,Festimating councils face a funding gap
OL,14,Fof #4 billion over the next two years
OL,15,Fto continue services at current levels.
OL,17,FClive Betts, Labour chair of the
OL,18,Fcommittee, said: "There is an out-of-
OL,19,Fcontrol financial crisis in local
OL,20,Fcouncils across England.
OL,26,@zD@ROU
