OL,7,FThe government also controls annual
OL,8,Frises in council tax. In the last two
OL,9,Fyears authorities must hold a local
OL,10,Freferendum if they wish to increase
OL,11,Fcouncil tax beyond 5%. The committee
OL,12,Fsaid this approach is "restricting
OL,13,Flocal authorities' abilities to raise
OL,14,Fsufficient funding to fulfil their
OL,15,Fstatutory responsibilities".
OL,17,FThe committee called for the
OL,18,Frevaluation of properties and the
OL,19,Fintroduction of additional council tax
OL,20,Fbands.
